The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 4: The RBI has warned that government finances would come under pressure because of the Sixth Pay Commission recommendations, a farm-loan waiver and subsidies. The central bank said it would continue with the tight monetary policy. Projecting eight per cent economic growth, the bank said the overall stance of the monetary policy would be to ensure a monetary and interest rate environment that prioritises price stability.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 4: The government has approved 17 foreign direct investment (FDI) proposals worth Rs 1,844.32 crore, including Rs 781-crore plan of Quippo Telecom.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 4: Sun Pharmaceuticals said the open offer for purchase of all outstanding shares of Taro has been extended to October 3 with a possibility of further extension, pursuant to an order by the Israeli supreme court.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 4: Tata Power Company will acquire a10 per cent stake in Australias Geodynamics Ltd for approximately Rs 165 crore.                            
	 Calcutta, Sept. 4: Eveready Industries India Ltd has announced the suspension of work at its Cossipore plant with effect from September 4 until further orders.                                                                                                                         
